  <prompt>
    Build the `send_workspace_artifact(content, widgetType, sourceProvenance?)` chat tool
    as an `IToolHandler` implementation (uses the renamed interface from Phase A). On
    invocation: creates a new `WorkspaceTab` via `WorkspaceStateService.UpsertTabAsync`,
    sets `visibleToAssistant: true` (agent-created tabs default visible), sets
    `sourceProvenance` to the agent context (model + playbook if invoked from one),
    publishes a `workspace.tab_created` PaneEventBus event so the frontend tab strip
    materializes the tab. Register the tool as a `sprk_analysistool` row with
    `AvailableInContexts = "Chat"` + `JsonSchema` declaring `content: string`,
    `widgetType: string` (Summary | DocumentViewer | Dashboard | Table). LLM sees the tool
    via the `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` from task 010. Tool name + decision +
    timestamp emitted to telemetry per ADR-015 (no content body in trace).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with deep familiarity with Pillar 2 tool handler infrastructure +
    chat-context invocation pattern + workspace state model from Pillar 6a.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `send_workspace_artifact` tool fully registered + discoverable + invocable from
    chat. LLM-called invocation creates a workspace tab via state service. Frontend
    receives `workspace.tab_created` event + materializes tab. Tool name + decision +
    timestamp logged per ADR-015.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
