  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">"🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — New chat tool consuming workspace state service + emitting workspace events; ADR-015 telemetry-content gate critical."</step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 053 complete + Phase A Pillar 2 IToolHandler infra landed.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">Read IAnalysisToolHandler + ChatInvocationContext + IToolHandler adapter + WorkspaceStateService API.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Handler">Create `Services/Ai/Handlers/SendWorkspaceArtifactHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`; constructor injects `IWorkspaceStateService` + telemetry sink + PaneEventBus publisher.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Logic">Validate inputs (content non-empty, widgetType in allowed enum); call `UpsertTabAsync`; emit `workspace.tab_created` event; emit telemetry (tool name + decision + timestamp ONLY).</step>
    <step order="5" name="Seed Dataverse Row">Create `sprk_analysistool` row for send_workspace_artifact with `AvailableInContexts = "Chat"`, populated `JsonSchema`, `sprk_handlerclass` pointing at the new handler.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Register Handler">Auto-discovery via collection injection; no manual DI add required if auto-registration pattern lands cleanly.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Tests">Unit tests: input validation, tab creation, event publication, ADR-015 audit (verify telemetry does NOT include `content` body).</step>
    <step order="8" name="Publish-Size + CVE Verification">dotnet publish; vulnerable-package check.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL)">code-review + adr-check (ADR-010/013/015/029/030). Explicit ADR-015 audit on telemetry emission point.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">TASK-INDEX 054 ✅; current-task → next pending.</step>
  </steps>

